Full disclosure: it's probably been 10+ years since I've last stepped foot in a Taco Bell, and it will likely be another 10+ before I do so again. I jokingly suggested we get a snack at TB this afternoon and my boyfriend pulled into the parking lot to call my bluff. My dad enjoys their bean burritos from time to time, so hey, why not. Upon seeing the menu I recalled all those commercials for the Doritos taco and gave it a whirl — gross. Aside from being neon orange and covered in some vague powder, the shell had no further resemblance to Doritos. Utterly bland, no cheesy zing to speak of. The rest of our order was equally discouraging (steak chalupa and chicken quesadilla). TB isn't for me. The bathrooms were atrocious and the service was delightful.
